Counting Palm Tree from Satellite image¶

This is an attempt to count palm tree from satellite image. Few palm tree image will be use as samples, match it to a palm tree farm satellite image, then capture & count palm trees in the farm.

Match template with scikit-image¶

Sample image will be match with full image using normalized correlation.

In [6]:
from skimage.feature import match_template

result_list = []
for i in range(sample_count):
    result_list.append(match_template(full_img, sample_img[i]))
print('Matches %s sample images to full image, to get correlations.' % len(result_list))

Matches 6 sample images to full image, to get correlations.

Filter high correlation result to get data point¶

Challenges:¶

With low pixel image download from Google search. Correlation thresholds need to be set with trial and error test. Because of low pixel image, correlation thresholds have to be low, enabling capture more data point. However, a low correlation threshold may cause wrong data point captured. This stage will be revisit to find optimum result.

In [7]:
filter_result = []
filter_result.append(np.where(result_list[0]>0.35))
filter_result.append(np.where(result_list[1]>0.35))
filter_result.append(np.where(result_list[2]>0.30))
filter_result.append(np.where(result_list[3]>0.30))
filter_result.append(np.where(result_list[4]>0.30))
filter_result.append(np.where(result_list[5]>0.30))

Clean up duplicate data point¶

Data point are captured from multiple samples, same data point may captured multiple time, which can cause duplicate. Clean up is needed. When multiple data point captured is too near in range, we can ignore it. Only capture the first data point.

In [11]:
n = 0
m = 0
captured = ([],[])
for i in range(len(result[0])):
    this = result[0][i]
    if this not in range(m,n):
        captured[0].append(result[0][i])
        captured[1].append(result[1][i])
        m = this
        n = this + 4
captured =(np.asarray(captured[0]),np.asarray(captured[1]))

Palm Trees captured in Palm Tree Farm satellite image¶

As visualization shows, with low pixel image, is hard to capture all palm trees. There's also a few duplicate count even after data cleaning. Therefore number of palm tree count is inaccurate. However, we can expect to have higher accuracy with high pixel image.
